<main id="services-methodology-content">
    <section class="tm-bg-01 tm-sect-01">
        <div class="container">
            <h3 class="tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-normal"><strong>It all starts with a solid foundation.</strong></h3>
            <p class="tm-default-p tm-margin-01">Our process is built on top of a decades-strong infrastructure, which includes rock-solid relationships with our team members, some of whom have been with us for over a decade. Only then can a well-defined methodology make a difference.</p>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="tm-bg-01">
        <div class="tm-wrapper">
            <div class="tm-our-process-img-01">
                <div class="container tm-zindex100 tm-sect-02 text-center">
                    <h3 class="tm-titlecolor tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-normal"><strong>“Real artists ship.”</strong></h3>
                    <p class="tm-titlecolor tm-default-p tm-nomargin">&mdash; Steve Jobs</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="tm-overlay-02"></div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="tm-sect-01 tm-bg-01 tm-our-process-img-02">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="tm-cell-block-01">
                <div class="tm-cell">
                    <img src="img/our-process/our-process-discovery.svg" alt="Discovery and request analysis" />
                </div>
                <div class="tm-cell">
                    <h3 class="text-uppercase tm-text-line-13"><strong>Discovery requirements elicitation?</strong></h3>
                    <p class="tm-default-p tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-15">It all begins with the Discovery Phase. We initiate an intensive, one to two weeks, discovery sprint organized to help our team grasp the core components of the business, gain industry specific knowledge, and most importantly understand your technical requirements precisely and completely. Here you work with your PYTEX Business Analyst, Project Manager and a dedicated Software Architect. At some point within this phase, we add the UI expert, UX expert, and your future Lead developer to attend discovery workshops, but all team members can be included as well, if the project requires full involvement of all team members from early discovery sessions. This workshop can be held in our sales offices in Chicago, New York, San Francisco, Toronto, London, or Sydney, or our development centers in Lviv, Sambir, Warsaw or Manila.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-5">
                    <p class="tm-default-p tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-15">The deliverables of this phase are properly formatted SCRUM user stories and journeys, which we document in Pivotal Tracker or Jira, or any other project management system of your choice. Based on these deliverables, we develop wireframes, UI/UX creative concepts, and any other creative documentation necessary at this phase.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-7 hidden-xs">
                    <div class="tm-cell-block-02 text-center">
                        <div class="tm-cell">
                            <img src="img/our-process/our-process-competitor-analysis.svg" alt="Competition analysis" />
                            <div><em>competition analysis</em></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tm-cell">
                            <img src="img/our-process/our-process-sitemap.svg" alt="Sitemap/workflow development" />
                            <div><em>sitemap/workflow development</em></div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="tm-cell">
                            <img src="img/our-process/our-process-wireframes.svg" alt="Wireframe development" />
                            <div><em>wireframe development</em></div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="tm-sect-07 tm-midline-01">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6 tm-block-01 tm-icon-writing">
                    <h3 class="text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-margin-01 tm-overflow-hidden">
                        <strong><span>user stories</span></strong>
                    </h3>
                    <p class="tm-default-p tm-text-line-15 tm-nomargin">We help you write solid user stories and user journeys of your future product, in proper SCRUM format, to ensure your functionality is easily described to the rest of the team members for best collaboration.</p>
                    <hr class="tm-hr-02 hidden-md hidden-lg"/>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 tm-block-02">
                    <div class="tm-cell-block-01">
                        <div class="tm-cell tm-margin-01">
                            <img src="img/our-process/our-process-user-stories.svg" alt="User stories" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="tm-cell">
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-infocolor tm-nomargin tm-text-line-13"><strong>User Story Format:</strong></p>
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-13">As a [who] I want to [what] so that [why].</p>
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-infocolor tm-nomargin tm-text-line-13"><strong>User Story Example:</strong></p>
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-nomargin tm-text-line-13">As a visitor-user I want to be able to post videos so I can share them with friends and friends of friends.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <hr class="tm-hr-02 hidden-md hidden-lg"/>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6 tm-block-01 tm-icon-refinement">
                    <div class="tm-cell-block-01">
                        <div class="tm-cell tm-margin-01">
                            <img src="img/our-process/our-process-backlog-clipboard.svg" alt="Backlog" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="tm-cell">
                            <h3 class="text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-margin-01 tm-overflow-hidden"><strong><span>Backlog</span></strong></h3>
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-15">Once we have the backlog of user stories, the team estimates the complexity of each user story. Here the Product Owner and the Team define user story details: goal, process, expectations, description, acceptance criteria, etc.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tm-cell-block-01">
                        <div class="tm-cell tm-margin-01">
                            <img src="img/our-process/our-process-backlog-estimation.svg" alt="Backlog estimation" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="tm-cell">
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-infocolor tm-nomargin tm-text-line-13"><strong>User Story Estimation</strong></p>
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-nomargin tm-text-line-15">The team collectively estimates complexity of each user story and divides the stories amongst each other.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <hr class="tm-hr-02 hidden-md hidden-lg"/>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 tm-block-02 tm-icon-planning">
                    <img class="img-responsive tm-margin-01" src="img/our-process/our-process-sprint-planning.svg" alt="Sprint planning" />
                    <h3 class="text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-margin-01 tm-overflow-hidden">
                        <strong><span>Sprint planning</span></strong>
                    </h3>
                    <p class="tm-default-p tm-text-line-15 tm-nomargin">Before every sprint, a Sprint Planning Meeting (SPM) is held. Here, the Product Owner prioritizes by importance all User Stories previously defined and estimated in the Backlog Refinement meetings. Based on their previous experience and estimated effort for each user story, the team agrees on the number of user stories that they can commit to completing in each sprint. Pivotal Tracker also programmatically suggests the number of stories to be delivered per week, based on previous weeks' velocity data.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="tm-accent-03 tm-midline-02">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6 tm-block-03 tm-titlecolor">
                    <h3 class="text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-margin-01 tm-overflow-hidden">
                        <strong><span>Sprint: <br/>repeat X times</span></strong>
                    </h3>
                    <p class="tm-default-p tm-text-line-15 tm-nomargin">The proper SCRUM process is executed in a number of iterations called Sprints. Each sprint is started by a Sprint Planning Meeting (SPM) in order to determine a sprint backlog - a list of the tasks to be performed during the sprint, and specific goals to be attained by the end of the sprint.</p>
                    <hr class="tm-hr-05 hidden-md hidden-lg"/>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 tm-block-03 tm-titlecolor">
                    <div class="tm-cell-block-01">
                        <div class="tm-cell tm-margin-01">
                            <img src="img/our-process/our-process-daily-meeting.svg" alt="Daily meeting" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="tm-cell">
                            <h3 class="h5 text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-margin-01 tm-overflow-hidden"><strong><span>Daily stand-up meeting</span></strong></h3>
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-13">We start every morning with an internal stand-up meeting to assess the progress. The meetings take no longer than 15 minutes, all members come prepared with the updates and every member is asked the following questions:</p>
                            <ul class="tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-13">
                                <li>What have you accomplished yesterday to achieve the goal?</li>
                                <li>What is your plan for today?</li>
                                <li>Are there any roadblocks that could jeopardise the deliverable?</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-13">If an issue is identified, before it grows into a problem it is collectively solved without disturbing the process.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="tm-sect-07 tm-midline-01">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-md-6 tm-block-01 tm-icon-review">
                    <div class="tm-cell-block-01">
                        <div class="tm-cell tm-margin-01">
                            <img src="img/our-process/our-process-sprint-review.svg" alt="Sprint review" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="tm-cell">
                            <h3 class="text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-margin-01 tm-overflow-hidden"><strong><span>Sprint review</span></strong></h3>
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-15">Inspect and improve <strong class="text-uppercase">the product.</strong></p>
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-15">This is the time for the team to demonstrate the work done within the iteration, get immediate feedback from project stakeholders and the Product Owner, and celebrate the team's accomplishments.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <hr class="tm-hr-02 hidden-md hidden-lg"/>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 tm-block-02 tm-icon-retrospective">
                    <img class="img-responsive tm-margin-01" src="img/our-process/our-process-sprint-retrospective.svg" alt="Sprint retrospective" />
                    <h3 class="text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-margin-01 tm-overflow-hidden">
                        <strong><span>Sprint retrospective</span></strong>
                    </h3>
                    <p class="tm-default-p tm-margin-01 tm-text-line-15">Here we inspect and improve <strong class="text-uppercase">the process.</strong></p>
                    <p class="tm-default-p tm-text-line-15 tm-nomargin">During the Sprint Assessment (SA) meeting, the team has an opportunity to openly express their thoughts on the sprint cycle. We discuss what went well and what can be improved in the following sprint. The things we learn during the Sprint Assessment meeting provide valuable information for continuous optimization of our processes.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row tm-sect-03">
                <div class="col-md-6 tm-block-01 tm-icon-product">
                    <p class="h5 text-uppercase tm-infocolor tm-margin-less"><strong>Shippable deliverable:</strong></p>
                    <h3 class="text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-margin-01 tm-overflow-hidden">
                        <strong><span>Product increment</span></strong>
                    </h3>
                    <p class="tm-default-p tm-text-line-15 tm-nomargin">Every sprint must deliver a usable and shippable product component, even as a basic first iteration.</p>
                    <hr class="tm-hr-02 hidden-md hidden-lg"/>
                </div>
                <div class="col-md-6 tm-block-02 tm-responsive">
                    <div class="tm-cell-block-01 tm-nomargin">
                        <div class="tm-cell tm-margin-01">
                            <img src="img/our-process/our-process-responsive-screens.svg" alt="Responsive screens" />
                        </div>
                        <div class="tm-cell">
                            <h3 class="h5 text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-margin-01 tm-overflow-hidden">
                                <strong><span>Responsive all-around</span></strong>
                            </h3>
                            <p class="tm-default-p tm-nomargin tm-text-line-15">Everything we build for the web is responsive in nature and adapts to screen resolutions, browsers, and operating systems. We go even further. Every project we build has an API component (usually node.js API) which makes app development a breeze.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    <div class="tm-bg-01">
        <div class="container tm-sect-01">
            <div class="col-md-5">
                <h1 class="h2 text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-nomargin"><strong>Strategy Development and Planning</strong></h1>
                <hr class="tm-hr-04"/>
                <img class="img-responsive" src="img/services/strategic-planning-services.svg" alt="Strategic Planning Services" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <p class="tm-increased tm-colored">There is an old quote by Benjamin Franklin that says: <strong>“By failing to prepare, you are preparing to fail."</strong></p>
                <p>We stand 100% behind that quote and we consider it a privilege to help you implement and merge your initial concept with everything our team knows about social networks, mobile, startups; about what does and doesn't work.</p>
                <p>Our team has experience working with small businesses and large corporations on a variety of projects. From basic to advanced requirements, we can provide the appropriate service to meet your needs.</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>How much will it cost?</strong></p>
                <p>
                    <strong>It's included.</strong><br/>
                    Our job is not just to complete a project, we are here for you to help you realise your vision. We will ask the right questions, discuss your business model, target market and strategic techniques; perhaps challenge your whole idea and then build together a safe and doable strategy that will help you earn a strongly-defined space in the digital world.
                </p>
                <p>It is also available as a separate service.</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>What does it look like?</strong></p>
                <ol>
                    <li>We go through your business model or help you create one.</li>
                    <li>We assemble all necessary information into an architecture, which can be a prototype or a wireframe</li>
                    <li>We discuss it together, gather feedback and finalise the strategy</li>
                    <li>We guide you through the process: investors, partners, work organisation, employees…</li>
                </ol>
                <p>With us you get way more than design and development. We have the experience, creativity and business savvy that you need to make your brand and product a success.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container tm-sect-01">
        <div class="col-md-5">
            <h1 class="h2 text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-nomargin"><strong>Prototyping: Wireframes and Prototypes</strong></h1>
            <hr class="tm-hr-04"/>
            <img class="img-responsive" src="img/services/prototyping.svg" alt="Prototyping: Wireframes and Prototypes" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-7">
            <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>Why is prototyping important?</strong></p>
            <p>In theory, everything works fine, in practice, it doesn't. Without a prototype, we can't test your product until we've built it, and in today's business environment, to build a product before you've tested it is insane.</p>
            <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>How do we solve this problem effectively?</strong></p>
            <p>Your requirements may change drastically during the building process. To solve that we create wireframes and clickable prototypes to illustrate the features that will be placed on a page to visualise how all interface elements will work together. Our goal is to test them, learn from them, model the product while it is still young, and continue to test it throughout the process until we are completely satisfied with the outcome.</p>
            <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>The Prototyping Process</strong></p>
            <p>Prototyping is a set of activities during a three step process:</p>
            <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>1. Discovery Phase</strong></p>
            <p>A discovery phase can define all functionalities. We can provide a detailed information architecture which outlines user journeys and build wireframes that can later become clickable prototypes. If you are building a start-up and you need to attract investors, this is the MVP you will need for a pitch.</p>
            <p>Every discovery phase is different. A simple wireframe may be enough for some projects, a full design for a selected number of pages may be needed for others to create the right clickable prototype.</p>
            <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>2. Review Phase</strong></p>
            <p>In this phase we present the prototype to you and we evaluate together whether the needs and expectations are met. This phase is crucial for determining what stays and what goes.</p>
            <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>3. Refinement Phase</strong></p>
            <p>This is the part where we gather feedback, identify areas that need to be perfected, or further defined and clarified, and continue modeling the product.</p>
            <p>They say that a picture is worth a thousand words. By creating a prototype we discuss the product through visuals instead of words which ensures that everyone shares a common understanding, and it reduces risk and avoids missed requirements, leading to a better design faster.</p>
            <p>That is why we build prototypes.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tm-bg-01">
        <div class="container tm-sect-01">
            <div class="col-md-5">
                <h1 class="h2 text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-nomargin"><strong>Branding</strong></h1>
                <hr class="tm-hr-04"/>
                <img class="img-responsive" src="img/services/corporate-identity-and-brand-design.svg" alt="Corporate Identity and Brand Design" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>The way your brand is perceived is essential to your business.</strong></p>
                <p>You have spent way too much time developing your company, defining your needs and values to flush it all down the toilet with mediocre design that is templated, old-fashioned and dull. Or even stolen!</p>
                <p><strong>Every bit of contact that you have with the public, whether they are your customers, stakeholders or just interested parties is marketing.</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your message is important!</li>
                    <li>Your logo is important!</li>
                    <li>Your website is important!</li>
                    <li>Your stationery is important!</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>Design is not just a pretty face, but rather the core, the DNA, of a brand.</strong></p>
                <p><strong>So what do we do? We ask the right questions:</strong></p>
                <p>
                    What drives customers to your brand? <br/>
                    What makes them buy from you or use your product? <br/>
                    What do they like about doing business with you?
                </p>
                <p>At EtonDigital we believe that successful brand design is about promoting business strengths and all of the above questions help us to develop the look, feel and messages behind your corporate identity so that we can start to build and communicate your brand.</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>Our corporate identity and branding consultancy includes:</strong></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Developing slogans and tag lines </li>
                    <li>Designing logos and corporate identities </li>
                    <li>Stationery design </li>
                    <li>On-going brand implementation across websites, literature and advertising</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>Delivery phases</strong></p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>1. Research</strong></p>
                <p>Information gathering phase. We research the market and competitive landscape, analyse your goals and objectives that will guide us through an effective campaign to deliver design and content.</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>2. Creating and conceptualization</strong></p>
                <p>Critical thinking phase. We assemble the gathered data, learn from it and develop a conceptual, strategised approach. The conceptualization and sketching will be based upon your strengths and unique selling points. This is a phase where we explore the right colour, type treatment, look and feel of the design.</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>3. Presentation</strong></p>
                <p>Designs will be presented in a mockup form for your review. We then discuss the feedback and this helps us provide a better sense of what the designs will look like in real life application or as part of a cohesive brand.</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>4. Revisions</strong></p>
                <p>Upon your feedback, any necessary changes to the presented designs will be addressed (i.e. color, type, graphic modification).</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>5. Finalization</strong></p>
                <p>When you are completely satisfied, designs are the finalised and delivered for print production, media outputs, online integration or media presentation, as needed.</p>
                <p><strong>Talk to us if you’d like to find out how our corporate identity and brand consultancy can help you develop more business.</strong></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container tm-sect-01">
        <div class="col-md-5">
            <h1 class="h2 text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-nomargin"><strong>Copywriting and Content Writing</strong></h1>
            <hr class="tm-hr-04"/>
            <img class="img-responsive" src="img/services/copywriting.svg" alt="Copywriting and Content Writing" />
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-7">
            <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>Is your goal to turn your visitors into leads?</strong></p>
            <p>Many businesses make the mistake of giving a copywriter's job to a random person. The result is a lot of jargon filled, business oriented text that no one wants to read. We find it baffling.</p>
            <p>People spend a lot of money building and improving their on-line presence and then spoil it all with poor, or mediocre at best, copy.</p>
            <p>We here at Eton Digital take great pride in delivering the whole package: clever strategy, great design and efficient development, and we find that many digital solutions on the web, are not as effective without a good copy.</p>
            <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>So what do we do?</strong></p>
            <p>We save you time: As you have already filled out our questionnaire we have a thorough understanding of what you want, making it easy for us to meet your needs and create effective, appropriate copy for your product.</p>
            <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>How does this work?</strong></p>
            <p>Whether it is website copy, a description for the App Stores, or a copy for your e-mail campaign we will:</p>
            <ol>
                <li>Research your target group: What type of tone they like, what questions they want answered</li>
                <li>Write clever copy with a good call to action</li>
                <li>Optimise it correctly</li>
            </ol>
            <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>Why is copywriting important?</strong></p>
            <p>A beautiful website is not enough to convey your message. Being in the top three search results or having a lovely ad is not enough to sell. Many companies have forgotten how important copy is, and have buried themselves in an endless sea of poorly written text. Don't be one of them.</p>
            <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>Has copywriting changed?</strong></p>
            <p>
                Yes.<br/>
                Copywriting on the Internet is greatly influenced by what people search for. With Google now rewarding pages that provide excellent user experience, many online businesses have turned to copywriters to make sure their visitors get what they came for. Good copywriters do their homework, they use available tools to check what people are searching for, what they share on their social media and what makes one business more successful than the other. And then they phrase it effectively.
            </p>
            <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>How much will it cost?</strong></p>
            <p>We would like you to have that competitive advantage and succeed, so we will offer you the best value for money and work within your budget. You can ask us for a quote free of charge.</p>
            <p>We can accommodate your every need, as one of our greatest strengths is the ability to deliver the whole package. Come to Eton Digital, and let us take care of everything.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="tm-bg-01">
        <div class="container tm-sect-01">
            <div class="col-md-5">
                <h1 class="h2 text-uppercase tm-text-line-normal tm-nomargin"><strong>Social Networks Development</strong></h1>
                <hr class="tm-hr-04"/>
                <img class="img-responsive" src="img/services/social-networking-design-development.svg" alt="Social Networking Design Development" />
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-7">
                <p><strong>If you're looking to build the next facebook, or a micro-social network for your industry, we're just the right team for you.</strong></p>
                <p class="tm-increased">We have a whole department dedicated to development of social networking websites and projects which are social in nature. On top of aesthetics, we deem performance as one of the most important and increasingly vital qualities of our projects. By using technologies such as Node.js (Loopback, Express.js), Angular.js, MongoDB, and AWS we ensure your social network is always lightning fast, loading in microseconds and seamlessly delivers the best user experience.</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>What do you get?</strong></p>
                <p><strong>A social network</strong> solution that is entirely and genuinely yours: custom look and feel, custom functionality, custom layout, and pretty much everything custom.</p>
                <p><strong>A team,</strong> which not only understands how to design, build and deploy social networks, elearning platforms, marketplaces, and pretty much anything social in nature, but also can help you grow, support, market and even raise VC for your project. We have done it time and time again and now offer a lot more than just technical and project management expertise to our valuable clients.</p>
                <p><strong>Full ownership</strong> of your intellectual property, which you have full control over at every step of the way, every sprint, every iteration, every phase. While it remains yours, we value your IP as we would our own.</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-colored"><strong>General Architectural Overview:</strong></p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>AngularJS web front-end and Apps</strong></p>
                <p>Most of our social networks use AngularJS on the front-end, aside from your usual HTML5, CSS3, and SCSS and/or SASS. AngularJS is by far the very best front-end framework for web application development and we have professionals who live and breathe Angular.</p>
                <p>Applications built with AngularJS save bandwidth as only data is being transferred, without the heavy wrappers around it. Separation of front-end and back-end logic results in maximum efficiency of hardware resources.</p>
                <p>Youtube, Vevo, MSNBC are just a few of the names heavily relying on AngularJS to provide quality services to their users.</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>API: Node.js (ExpressJS, Loopback, MongoDB, SwaggerUI)</strong></p>
                <p>API is what glues your front-end views with the back-end data and logic. The technologies we use can support billions of simultaneous connections with the right hardware behind them (usually AWS).</p>
                <p>If required, we also have PHP(Yii) and Python(django) back-end libraries to support your application requirements. Every solution is different and we make sure the technology stack fits just right.</p>
                <p class="tm-increased tm-margin-less"><strong>AWS</strong></p>
                <p>We are entirely cloud oriented. We understand AWS inside out and use the whole spectrum of its services: from Route53 and CloudFront, to proper load balancing and auto-scaling EC2 instances and RDS instances, all the way through to proper deployment via Elastic Beanstalk and OpsWorks.</p>
